  "text": "Raltegravir and the investigational integrase inhibitor elvitegravir impede viral replication by preventing integrase strand transfer in the nucleus of the infected cells. QNL111, a member of the quinoline family, inhibits HIV-1 integrase binding to its substrate, an early step in integration. Fluorescence anisotropy confirmed that QNL111 prevents integrase-DNA binding, whereas raltegravir acts on the preformed DNA-integrase complex. QNL111 antiviral activity measured as IC [CITATION_1] in HeLa P4/R5 cells was 0.83 µM, and in MT4 cells was 0.89 µM.",
